other_tests.procedure_name: Transsphenoidal resection of Rathke cleft cyst
other_tests.findings: Cyst contained thick, clear, mucoid liquid and a few opaque chunks of amorphous solid material. No cerebrospinal fluid leakage. No apparent residue on postoperative MR image.
Hamartoma was removed with normal-appearing neurons and variously prominent astrocytes visible. No seizures postoperatively.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Patient has been seizure free for 6 months postoperatively.

other_tests.findings: First lesion consistent with Rathke cleft cyst. Second lesion confirmed as hypothalamic hamartoma.
